<div class="policy-wrap">
<h2>What We Do</h2>
<p>DirectFlight.net is a global guide to nonstop flights. We cover routes, airlines, flight times, and tips for travelers who want to fly direct — from any major hub, to any destination, at any budget.</p>
<p>We're not a booking platform. We don't sell tickets. We research the routes, explain the options, and send you to trusted booking partners (like Skyscanner) when you're ready to buy.</p>
<h2>Why We Built It</h2>
<p>Finding genuine nonstop options used to require digging through flight search results littered with connections. The filters helped, but the context didn't exist — which airlines fly a route, how often, what the cabin products are like, when to book for the best price.</p>
<p>We built DirectFlight.net to be that context layer. A place where the answer to "is there a nonstop flight from Dubai to Sydney?" is a clear yes or no, with the airlines, frequency, and tips you need to actually book with confidence.</p>
<h2>How We Make Money</h2>
<p>We earn money two ways: affiliate commissions when you book through our partner links (at no extra cost to you), and advertising revenue through Google AdSense. Our content and route data are not influenced by either revenue stream. See our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for full details.</p>
<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Questions, corrections, or partnership enquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@directflight.net">hello@directflight.net</a></p>
</div>
